  "text": "Pandey and Rouselakis [CITATION_1] introduce the notion of property-preserving encryption (PPE): an encryption scheme where a public predicate can be tested on any k ciphertexts. OPE is a PPE for the order comparison predicate with k = 2. Pandey and Rouselakis [CITATION_2] provide a construction for the inner product predicate, but not for the order predicate.",
